cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on natural language processing tasks, specifically morphological reinflection, and proposes neural network approaches to tackle the task. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper heavily relies on neural network models. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with automated language processing tasks. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper proposes neural network architectures. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper experiments with character alignment and proposes a neural state-transition system over a set of explicit edit actions.
